author: HERALD AND NEWS STAFF
title: Klamath Basin roundup: Davis Hartwell falls in round of 32 at U.S. Junior Amateur | Sports | heraldandnews.com
text:
Davis Hartwell's run at the U.S. Junior Amateur came to an end in the round of 32.
Hartwell, a junior-to-be at Crosspoint Christian in Klamath Falls, suffered a 4 and 2 loss to No. 26 Matthew Diehl of Redlands, Calif., on Thursday morning at Oakland Hills Country Club in Bloomfield Township, Mich.
